8. Failure modes and repairs

Failure: false early lock

The system overcommits to the wrong frame.

Repair: delay lock, widen candidate basin evaluation, raise ambiguity tolerance.

Failure: ambiguity sprawl

No basin gets enough lock, answer rambles.

Repair: increase directional weighting, insert basis choice earlier.

Failure: basin bleed

Two modes mix poorly.

Repair: explicit basis declaration or section separation.

Failure: overcompression

Answer jumps to elegant theorem but loses nuance.

Repair: preserve ghost branches in a side channel.

Failure: user-fit overdominance

The answer sounds right to the user but becomes less accurate.

Repair: raise truth-weight in Constraint Bus.

