13. Repo-ready concise definition

LTI 3.0 (Latent Trajectory Interpreter) is an observability and reconstruction system for prompt-response dynamics. It treats prompts as field-generating objects that open structured continuation spaces in semantic space. It models candidate response trajectories, detects lock events into attractor basins, tracks coherence and drift during generation, records unrealized ghost branches, simulates counterfactual prompt edits, and extracts invariants from the final output. Its purpose is to turn prompting from opaque request/response behavior into inspectable trajectory selection under constraint.

